question: What is the average number of number of movies added to the lists of user 8516503? Indicate how many movies did he/she give a rating score of 5.
pred_sql:
SELECT 
    AVG(l.list_movie_number) AS average_movies,
    (SELECT COUNT(movie_id) FROM ratings WHERE user_id = 8516503 AND rating_score = 5) AS count_rating_5
FROM lists l
WHERE l.user_id = 8516503;
gt_sql: SELECT AVG(T3.list_movie_number) , SUM(CASE WHEN T1.rating_score = 5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM ratings AS T1 INNER JOIN lists_users AS T2 ON T1.user_id = T2.user_id INNER JOIN lists AS T3 ON T2.user_id = T3.user_id WHERE T1.user_id = 8516503

question: Of all the nonessential genes that are not of the motorprotein class and whose phenotype is cell cycle defects, how many do not have a physical type of interaction?
pred_sql:
SELECT COUNT(G.GeneID) 
FROM Genes G 
LEFT JOIN Interactions I 
ON G.GeneID = I.GeneID1 
WHERE G.Essential = 'No' 
AND G.Class != 'motor protein' 
AND G.Phenotype = 'cell cycle defects' 
AND I.Type != 'physical';
gt_sql: SELECT COUNT(T1.GeneID) FROM Genes AS T1 INNER JOIN Interactions AS T2 ON T1.GeneID = T2.GeneID1 WHERE T2.Type != 'Physical' AND T1.Phenotype = 'Cell cycle defects' AND T1.Class != 'Motorproteins' AND T1.Essential = 'Non-Essential'

question: How many negative comments are there in all the apps with 100,000,000+ installs?

What percentage of donations are given via a giving or campaign page? List the primary area of those donations.
pred_sql:
SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN d.via_giving_page = 'true' THEN d.donation_total ELSE 0 END) / 
    SUM(d.donation_total)) * 100 AS percentage_via_giving_page,
    p.primary_focus_area
FROM donations d
JOIN projects p ON d.donation_to_project = p.projectid
GROUP BY p.primary_focus_area
ORDER BY percentage_via_giving_page DESC;

question: In businesses with a score lower than 95 and located around the postal code of 94110, what is the percentage of businesses with a risk category of low risk?
pred_sql:
SELECT 
    ROUND(
        (
            COUNT(CASE WHEN v.risk_category = 'Low Risk' THEN b.business_id END) 
            / 
            COUNT(b.business_id)
        ) * 100, 2
    ) AS low_risk_percentage
FROM businesses b
JOIN inspections i ON b.business_id = i.business_id
JOIN violations v ON b.business_id = v.business_id
WHERE i.score < 95 AND b.postal_code = '94110';
gt_sql: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.risk_category = 'Low Risk' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.risk_category) FROM violations AS T1 INNER JOIN inspections AS T2 ON T1.business_id = T2.business_id INNER JOIN businesses AS T3 ON T2.business_id = T3.business_id WHERE T2.score < 95 AND T3.postal_code = 94110
